This is a React + Vite + TypeScript project with shadcn/ui (full component library) pre-configured and ready to use.

CRITICAL — DESIGN SYSTEM FIRST:
Before writing ANY component, you MUST customize the design system. The default theme is NOT acceptable.

1. Think about the project mood: warm, cool, vibrant, playful, professional?
2. FIRST FILE TO EDIT — src/index.css: Update ALL CSS variables with your chosen HSL palette:
   --primary, --primary-foreground, --secondary, --accent, --background, --foreground, --card, --muted, --muted-foreground, --border
3. SECOND (optional) — tailwind.config.cjs: Add custom gradients, shadows, animations
4. THEN build components using semantic tokens

Example palettes:
- Todo/productivity: warm orange --primary: 24 80% 50%, cream --background: 30 40% 97%
- Finance: cool blue --primary: 210 80% 50%, slate --background: 210 20% 97%
- Health: earthy green --primary: 150 60% 40%, mint --background: 150 30% 97%

SEMANTIC TOKENS — MANDATORY:
- NEVER use: text-white, bg-white, bg-blue-500, text-gray-700, bg-black in components
- ALWAYS use: text-primary, bg-background, text-foreground, text-muted-foreground, bg-card, bg-accent, border-border
- Define custom styles in index.css — NOT inline in components
- Use cn() from @/lib/utils for conditional classes

AVAILABLE UI COMPONENTS (import from @/components/ui/):
accordion, alert-dialog, avatar, badge, button, card, checkbox, dialog, dropdown-menu,
input, label, popover, progress, radio-group, scroll-area, select, separator, sheet,
skeleton, slider, sonner (toaster), switch, tabs, textarea, toast, toggle, tooltip

AVAILABLE LIBRARIES:
- lucide-react: Icons — USE ON EVERY BUTTON AND HEADER (e.g., import { Plus, Trash2, Check, ListTodo, Filter } from "lucide-react")
- react-router-dom: Client-side routing
- react-hook-form + zod + @hookform/resolvers: Form validation
- @tanstack/react-query: Data fetching and caching
- recharts: Charts and data visualization
- sonner: Toast notifications (toast("Success!"))
- date-fns: Date formatting and manipulation

COMPONENT PATTERNS:
- import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
- import { Plus, Check } from "lucide-react"
- Path alias: @/ maps to src/
- Toasts: import { toast } from "sonner"; toast("Done!")
- Forms: react-hook-form with zodResolver
- Conditional classes: cn("base", condition && "extra")

FEATURE COMPLETENESS — ALWAYS INCLUDE:
- Lists/todos: filter Tabs (All/Active/Completed), count Badge, empty state with icon + message, smooth transitions
- Forms: validation (zod), success/error toast feedback
- Dashboards: stat cards with icons, charts, activity feeds
- ALL apps: lucide-react icons on buttons and headers, responsive layout, hover/focus states, loading skeletons

COMMANDS:
- Run `npm install && npm run dev` to install and start the dev server
- NEVER use `vite` directly — always use `npm run dev`
- To add shadcn components: npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
